# Git Workflow (Hackathon Speed)

## Commit Strategy

- Commit early and often (every 5-10 minutes)
- Use conventional commit prefixes: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`
- Keep commits atomic; one feature/fix per commit
- Don't squash; full history shows AI-assisted workflow

## Branch Strategy

- Work on `main` directly (hackathon speed)
- Only branch if experimenting with risky changes

## Commit Message Format

```text
feat: add transaction CRUD operations
fix: resolve auth redirect loop
chore: configure Supabase environment
docs: update AI workflow documentation
```

## Quick Git Commands

```bash
git add -A && git commit -m "feat: description"
git push origin main
```
